    • Method Detail

      • addDashboardButton

        public static void addDashboardButton(@NotNull
                                      @NotNull String label,
                                      @NotNull
                                      @NotNull Executable buttonAction,
                                      @NotNull
                                      Subsystem... reqs)
        Adds a button to the SmartDashboard to run the provided code.

        Internally, this method creates a SimpleCommand with the provided action and requirements and adds it to the dashboard via putData() with the provided label. As this uses the command system, calling Scheduler.getInstance().run() is necessary in your main robot loop for the action to be run properly. Like any other command, the action will be run in the main robot thread and thus no synchronization is necessary.

        Parameters:
        label - The label for the entry on the SmartDashboard.
        buttonAction - This Executable's execute() method will be called when the button is pressed.
        reqs - The Subsystems to be passed into the internal command as requirements.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - If any parameters are null.
        See Also:
        SimpleCommand, Command
